President Barack Obama has issued a proclamation declaring March 25, 2016, as Greek Independence Day: A National Day of Celebration of Greek and American Democracy. The proclamation highlights the close relationship between Greece and the United States, emphasizing the contributions of Greek Americans to American society. It also acknowledges the shared values and commitment to democracy that both countries hold. The proclamation recognizes the challenges faced by Greece, particularly in response to the ongoing refugee and migration crisis, and expresses solidarity and support. President Obama calls upon the people of the United States to observe the day with appropriate ceremonies and activities.